{
  "title": "Testing Strategies for Doctests with pytest in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides an overview of effective testing strategies for combining Doctests and pytest in Python 3.12+ to ensure robust testing of your code.",

  "key_points": [
    "Use both doctest and pytest to leverage the strengths of each testing approach",
    "Doctests should be used primarily for documentation and quick checks",
    "pytest should handle comprehensive, unit-level tests with fixture support",
    "Combine Doctests and pytest using pytest's built-in doctest plugin",
    "Exclude Doctests from standard test runs with pytest_ignore_doctests plugin"
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "def my_function(x):\n    '''Square root of a number\n       Returns the square root of x, raising ValueError if x is negative.''\n    from math import sqrt, isnan\n    \n    >>> assert my_function(4) == sqrt(16)\n    >>> assert my_function(-1) raises(ValueError)\n      ...\n      File \"<stdin>\", line 1\n        assert my_function(-1) raises(ValueError)\n      AssertionError: assert -1.0 == <built-in function sqrt> raised ValueError"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "import pytest\n\n@pytest.mark.doctest\ndef test_my_function():\n    \"\"\"Square root of a number\n       Returns the square root of x, raising ValueError if x is negative.\""\"'\n    from my_module import my_function\n    \n    pytest.check(my_function(4) == sqrt(16))\n    pytest.raises(ValueError, my_function, -1)"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Pytest 7.2.0 introduced built-in support for Doctests",
    "pytest_ignore_doctest is available from third-party packages like pytest-skipdoctest"
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Doctests may not be comprehensive and should be supplemented with pytest tests for full coverage",
    "Pytest's Doctest integration can cause slower test runs, especially on larger projects",
    "Ensure that your Doctests are well-documented and self-contained to maintain clarity"
  ]
}
